	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Giant Spiders are the major (if not only) source of Spider Silk in Norrath -- used to make all sorts of raw silk armor by tailors.<BR>
<BR>
Often, although the venom sacs are worth 4 or 5 gp each to vendors, the spider silk can be worth a lot to a low level player -- since many tailors will pay between 3 and 10 gp per piece. (avg 5gp I'd say).  Other types of loot, like legs, can even make hunting these critters worthwhile.<BR>
<BR>
They're easiest to find in the Karanas and the Commonlands, although they are common on Faydwer as well (they're just hard to spot in the forest).
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
